    <title>About users, user roles and user groups</title>
    <para>Multiple users can access DHIS2 simultaneously and each user can have different
        permissions. You can fine-tune these permissions so that certain users can only enter data,
        while others can only generate reports.</para>
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>You can create as many user names
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161107T150034+0100" comment="User name = user?"?>as<?oxy_comment_end?>
                you need.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Each
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161107T150628+0100" comment="Directly on the user or via a user role?"?>user<?oxy_comment_end?>
                can be assigned certain privileges.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>You can create multiple user roles each with their own set of permissions.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Assign user roles to users to grant the users certain privileges within
                DHIS2.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>You can assign each user to certain
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161107T145705+0100" comment="The only thing that happens when you assign a user to an org unit? 
You don&apos;t have to do it?"?>organisation<?oxy_comment_end?>
                units
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161107T145336+0100" comment="Reword"?>for
                which they will be enabled to enter data on behalf of.<?oxy_comment_end?></para>
        </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
